                          History of DarkWind
========================================================================
 
     It is said that there was a time before Alarian DarkWind traveled the
known planes of existance, athough no historian or tome in existance has
ever been able to denote just when Alarian decided to take notice of
a small insignificant world known as Geshtei.  The reason Alarian did
take note of this planet was because it was the first such place he had
ever come across that was devoid of any type of godly influence, and the
desire to mold an entire world into his image was too intriguing for him
to ignore.  Many millennia passed before the first true signs of
intelligent life first appeared, and Alarian fostered these few creatures
and encouraged them to flourish.  As time wore on though, Alarian began
to become bored and decided to search his lands for someone with whom
he could speak.
        As fate would have it this person turned out to be a king of a
far off land by the name of Balzar, Elder ruler of Hareth, a now long
dead kingdom.  Alarian spent much time with him, and when Balzar's years
began to catch up with him, and his health began to fail, he chose to
imbue him with some of his powers so that he could live on.  At first, it
was a small fraction of his own power, but as time wore on and Balzar began
spending more and more time carving out his own section of the world, it
became easier for Alarian to just give him the additional powers he needed
so that he would not have to keep assisting him in his endeavors.  But with
the additional powers, Balzar spent even more time at his tasks, and
once again Alarian became bored.  His next associate was a great sorceress
by the name of Talan.  She had been know across the land for several
centuries as the most powerful spell caster ever known, so Alarian chose
to once again imbue her with some of his power and raise her status above
that of a mere mortal.  But once again, after time, she began to carve
out her section of Geshtei into her own liking.  This process went on
for several centuries where Alarian would grant some of his powers to
those he felt were worthy to join his ranks.  One by one they joined him:
Antcrusher from the city of Lorkin who was known as one of the great
diplomats of his time.  Malruax, the greatest mortal Alarian had ever seen
when it came to using magic to create wonders out of almost nothing.  Rax,
another great mage skilled in finding the slightest imperfections in the
threads of reality and straightening them out to read as they should.
        For the most part, Alarian left these five to do as they desired,
but after time, he began to tire of the slow progress that was being
made in the world and called his five friends together to work as a
team to create the world as he envisioned it.  At first the progresses
seen were incredible, things that had taken him centuries to accomplish
were being accomplished in a single mortals lifetime, but also, he
could see that the visions of the others were working their way into
his plans.  At first he resisted, as some of these changes wiped out
work that had taken him many mortal lifetimes to accomplish, but as
time went on, he could see that many of these changes had previously
unseen benifits.  Civilization had moved out of the stages of
barbarianism in most places, and was just starting to enter into a time
of great properity.  Also, as time had progressed, Alarian had found it
easier to imbue his friends with even more power to allow them to do even
greater things to Geshtei, and many mortals now refered to them
as demigods.  But as time wore on, the cries of the mortals became to
bothersome, so Alarian chose to go back to the land of mortals and find a
few more others to become spokespersons for the laws that Alarian and his
now Demi-Gods decreed.  He chose five worthy mortals to fill his needs,
Dragoon, Hayden, Malcolm, Rodney, and Solon.  They all flourished in their new
positions and made it possible for the others to perform their tasks even
more efficiently.  Then out of a time before even the existance of life on
Geshtei an old friend of Alarian's appeared, Grayhawk.  He was also looking
for a simple place to spend time away from others of his kind.  Alarian
invited him to stay here, and he accepted.
        Much time has passed since the forming of the world, and lately a
small kingdom known as DarkWind has been the center of attention of all
the immortals.  For the first time in the history of Geshtei, Alarian,
Grayhawk, Balzar, Talan, Antcrusher, Malraux, and Rax have offered a
challenge to all the mortals of the land.  If they can succed in becoming
the most powerful person(s) in the land and also accomplish several Quests
designed by them, they will be elevated to the status of immortal and be
allowed to create a realm molded from their own desires.  So far, people from
all ends of Geshtei have traveled here to try and accomplish this task.  So
far, many have tried but only a few have succeeded.

